cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.PF

This paper discusses energy optimizations in content delivery networks (CDNs), which involves load balancing across multiple data centers and servers. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses hardware reliability and wear-and-tear, which suggests a possible fit with cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The focus on energy efficiency and optimization suggests a possible fit with cs.PF (Performance), while the discussion of SLAs and availability suggests a possible fit with cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the mention of data centers suggests a possible fit with cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
